    Bracket Grid

    Time limit: 500 ms
    Memory limit: 256 MB

    A bracket sequence SSS is a correct bracket sequence if either of the following holds :

    • It is empty.
    • It is the concatenation of 222 correct bracket sequences.
    • It is of the form (T)(T)(T), where TTT is a correct bracket sequence.

    For example, (()),(()()),(()(()))(()())(()), (()()), (()(()))(()())(()),(()()),(()(()))(()()) are correct bracket sequences while ())(,(()))(,()((,(())(, (()))(, ()((, (())(,(()))(,()((,( are not correct bracket sequences.

    Construct a grid where each cell is filled with either ((( or ))) such that there are exactly KKK paths from the top left corner to the bottom right corner which goes only downwards and rightwards, and the bracket sequence formed by the squares visited in the path is a correct bracket sequence.

    Standard input

    The first and only line of input contains a single integer KKK.

    Standard output

    The first line of output should contain two integers N,MN, MN,M, denoting the number of rows and the number of columns of the grid respectively.

    The next NNN should contain MMM characters each, where each character should be either ((( or ))). The output grid must contain exactly KKK paths from the top-left corner to the bottom-right corner which goes only downwards or rightwards such that the sequence of brackets formed from the path is a correct bracket sequence. If there are multiple solutions, any valid solution will be accepted.

    Constraints and notes

    • 1?K?1091 \le K \le 10^{9}1?K?10?9??
    • The output must satisfy 1?N,M?2001 \le N, M \le 2001?N,M?200.
